cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

The paper proposes a novel recurrent neural network architecture for processing sequential data, which is a common problem in a wide range of applications such as speech recognition, language modeling, generative image modeling, and machine translation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions empirical investigations of the learning and network dynamics of the proposed architecture, which suggests that it could be relevant to the sub-categories cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
